Help → Install New Software → Add repository from location: http://download.eclipse.org/egit/updates/

Select all, click next, agree to the license terms, and install
After restarting the Eclipse, add Git perspective.

now you need to share your project in the github.

1. right click on the project --> Team --> share project
2. create a repositry.
3. then click on commit.
4. click on ++ to stage all your changes.
5. enter commit message. 
6. enter your aurther and commiter and click on commit and push




